cs.CV, cs.MED, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.NA 

The paper discusses the fusion of MRI and TRUS data for prostate brachytherapy, which involves image processing and dosimetry evaluation. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computer vision (cs.CV) for image processing, medical imaging (cs.MED) for the application in brachytherapy, information retrieval (cs.IR) for the retrieval of relevant medical data, machine learning (cs.LG) for the development of algorithms, and numerical analysis (cs.NA) for the evaluation of dose planning. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
